<br>
1. At 18 you may be a little too young to tackle them. They will easily charm you, and you'll find yourself dying to your pet a lot. I'd wait until 21, I believe that's when you get your new nukes, plus you're big enough to resist the charms.<br>
<br>
2. If you're in a group, the charming situation is worse, because you'll be killed by your groupmates. Or, more often, you'll be KILLING your groupmates. A charmed magician is a terrible thing to behold.<br>
<br>
3. If you or your pet are charmed, and the evil eye is killed before the charm wears off, then the pet will go renegade. This means it will attack anybody that comes near it. If you've got a mean streak in you, train it to the Runnyeye entrance, but don't do this if you can help it. It's heartbreaking to see some poor shmoe zone from Runnyeye with a sliver of life, only to be put down by an angry elemental on the other side. (Heh, thanks to the scryer I had a renegade 34 fire pet running around Upper Guk the other day. Man, you should've heard some of the /oocs)<br>
<br>
4. The best way to deal with the eye seems to be to Bolt the eyeball while you put your pet on his pet. For best effect, attack before the eyeball has a pet. The eye will attack you, so be prepared for some DD pain and charm attempts. Two bolts will put most eyeballs down. More for the Lords.<br>
<br>
5. If the big one spawns in the middle (Lord Soptyver) you're done. Unless there's a high level there to clear him for you, he will aggro if you pull either eyeball.<br>
<br>
6. Roamers abound in the eyeball pit, watch out for them. Plus, the pathing is downright terrible. You will just have to go and learn from experience.<br>
 <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 37th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udristan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dristan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/00 6:02:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=106.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/games2/Drist/finish.GIF height=90 width=110></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Advice requested on Evil Eyes</span><hr size=1> charm is a nasty thing though ...  i have two good charm stories.<br>
