<br>
Once, charmed by an evil eye in Beholder Gorge and my pet dead, I stayed charmed for over 5 minutes. I couldn't believe how well that charm stuck. I followed the eyeball all around Beholder like a puppy dog. Every mob we met, the eye would Quickness them, then I would fire shield them, then we'd move on. It was hilarious.<br>
<br>
Another time, in another life, I was a paladin trying to fight a Tae Ew something or other that charmed in CT. He was surrounded by a mob of green things, some of which would heal him. Three times during the fight he stuck a charm to me, and while I was charmed the lizards would heal me back to full. Then the charm broke and I'd go back to fighting the Tae thingy. I was able to win the fight only because of those lizards healing me up.<br>
<br>
Being charmed can be scary, but sometimes it can be entertaining, too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 39th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unabienincinerador.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nabien Incinerador</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/fire10.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/00 7:19:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=106.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/explose3.gif WIDTH=96 HEIGHT=156></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Advice requested on Evil Eyes</span><hr size=1> I was in solB the other day going to help break the SS room and while we were still forming the group at the zone I saw the noble cast.  So feeling all mighty and powerful like any level 55 does against those kobalds, I summoned my pet and went after it.  Having 120 MR does NOT help if it tries to charm your pet and not you... I felt pretty embarassed telling my guild how I died...<br>
<br>
